@page "/"

<PageTitle>Two Rooms</PageTitle>

<div class="menu">
    <h1>Two Rooms</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">
        Asymmetric co-op games for two players. Join the same session code on two devices &mdash;
        you'll each see something different, so you'll need to talk to win.
    </p>

    <div class="game-list">
        <a class="game-card" href="duel">
            <div class="game-card-title">Reaction Duel</div>
            <div class="game-card-text">
                Both players see the same signal. First to react wins the round, best of 5 takes the match.
            </div>
        </a>
        <a class="game-card" href="maze">
            <div class="game-card-title">Maze Navigator</div>
            <div class="game-card-text">
                One player sees the maze but not their partner. The other can move but can't see the map.
            </div>
        </a>
        <a class="game-card" href="lock">
            <div class="game-card-title">Symbol Lock</div>
            <div class="game-card-text">
                One player sees symbols on a door, the other has the codex to decode them. Work out the code together.
            </div>
        </a>
        <a class="game-card" href="bomb">
            <div class="game-card-title">Bomb Defusal</div>
            <div class="game-card-text">
                One player sees the wires, the other has the rule manual. Work out which wire to cut before time runs out.
            </div>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
